node.text:
The outbreak of COVID-19 pandemic across the world has severely affected the normal functioning of various services. With the complete closure of some industries, the number of people losing their jobs is rapidly increasing. Assam’s mobile theatre industry is one such sector where almost 50 theatre groups perform all over the state but now is in a state of mere uncertainty. Each of these groups provides employment to 100 to 150 people, including artistes, pandal makers, light men, and sound men. Losing a day’s performance costs a financial loss of around Rs 1 lakh for an entire group.⠀
⠀
In a normal situation, these groups would have set out on a 9-month journey to perform in front of people in various districts of the state, in the first week of August. According to reports, many artists working in these theatre groups are now reaching out to people for donations as they have lost their only source of income during this tough time.⠀
⠀
Pathsala a town known to be the heart of mobile theatres in Assam is experiencing a silent ‘theatre season’ which the people of Pathsala has never experienced since 1963 when the mobile theatre was started by Achyut Lahkar.⠀
⠀

Do you remember when lockdown hit and the only sound was that of bird song in the trees?

Cycling has always been a passion of mine, but something i managed to let slip with work, life and moving to London. Finding freedom lacking I returned to cycling to find solice in the journey of riding for hours and not being fixated on any ultimate destination. Sometimes you just have to sing your own song in life and hope you remember the words, and not just focus on the chorus and fanfare when everyone else joins in.

Der Song "Sorry Mama" ist letzten Sommer entstanden: @bligg und @marc_sway hatten sich über die Welt und die Zukunft ihrer Kinder unterhalten. Die immer heisser werdenden Sommer und die Winter beinahe ohne Schnee konnten sie nicht mehr ignorieren und haben kurzerhand einen Song darüber geschrieben.
.
Dass dieses Lied kaum passender hätte sein können, zeigte sich im Frühling dieses Jahres, sie ihn erstmals am Swiss Music Award präsentierten. 
.
Der Videoclip dazu ist während dem Lockdown entstanden und zeigen Bilder einer Welt, die es so noch nie gegeben hat - und hoffentlich auch nie mehr geben wird.
.
Fazit: ein berührender Song über Mutter Erde mit einem epischen Videoclip... Gönn' dir diese fünf Minuten Gänsehaut!
.
.

node.text:
We often complain about our loved ones not helping us, not succeeding in understanding us.
What if they have tried their best and failed?
But still they want to try harder and harder till they succeed.
What If they had put all their energy to it and still failed?
And now they feel guilty of not helping us.

It's okay. It's really okay if they failed. What matters the most is that they tried. And how much effort they have given to it. What matters is their urge to help us, their want to make us feel better. Appreciate their efforts, appreciate that they cared of trying hard for us.

Always count efforts more than failures. Always leave space for second chances if in the first one they lost, even after trying harder.

.

.
.
.

TENETevi alla larga.
Non è colpa solo di Christopher Nolan, al quale auguro una pronta guarigione e tornare a dirigere capolavori come INTERSTELLAR, se Tenet è una gigantesca delusione. Un film onanistico, sterile, noioso, involuto e asettico. Il regista con Kubrick ha in comune solo il caratteraccio e il segno zodiacale, ma non la calma e l'ossessiva precisione. La fretta di farlo uscire nelle sale denota consapevolezza della pochezza del film, e voler sufrattare in ambi i sensi (successo per il desiderio di tornare al cinema o insuccesso per le condizioni in cui lo si fa), il periodo del post lockdown. Sostenevo che la colpa non è solo sua ma soprattutto della tecnologia che ha ucciso il cinema come lo conosciamo. Ha reso inutili tutti i movimenti di macchina pensati dal regista, che di fatto ha ceduto lo scettro alla post produzione. Questa a sua volta, come fanno gli enzimi, i fermenti e i lieviti selezionati, ha creato storie del tutto simili fra loro, predilegendo la trama fumettistica e imponendola anche ad altri generi. Ha obbligato l'eroe cinematografico a trasformarsi in un supereroe perché era l'unico modo di integrarlo in una storia infruttuosa e algida. Ha illuso che tutto ora sia descrivibile, non lasciando più sottintesi e in maniera implacabile e funesta ci mostra tutto come sarebbe. Ha accorciato i tempi di produzione di una pellicola uccidendo così gli imprevisti, la ponderazione, il ripensamento che una lenta concezione imponeva. Pertanto per salvare il cinema non vedo altra soluzione che di andare a vedere d'ora in poi esclusivamente i film d'autore, diretti con pochi mezzi e privi di effetti speciali. Altrimenti sarà la sua fine.

node.text:
Trying to scratch hard the surface of a rupee coin to check whether it turns to gold. That's what the past few days or weeks (let's just say months) have been. Like I exchanged my gold coin (imagination) with my plain colleague (rupee coin, who by the way is now very interested in the same cloud photography she ridiculed me for, a year ago). It's as if the imaginative grey cells within have got locked up (lock up courtesy: the lockdown), and trying to get them to work is proving impossible. (This theory in my view is more plausible, because I'm pretty sure imagination to like most other entities flows from higher to lower concentrations). 
The clouds just seem to be clouds, they no longer look like warm cosy blankets to cuddle in this pleasant rainy weather. The flowers are just flowers, well what else could they be (that's my mundane mind talking). It pains me, unexpectedly and beyond my understanding as to how and why I am unable to think of something, or rather anything. 
The question now is whether these little imaginative brain cells will come around when we go out and celebrate brighter days again, or whether they've shifted out of my mind palace lock, stock and barrel.

shortcode_media.title: Weight-bearing exercises on the Reformer Part 3: Long Stretch & Jackrabbit

node.text:
.
Here’s just one variation that leads on from what you’ve practiced in Quadruped & Reverse Abs. 
As I said it’s important to get the basics first before we increase the load and in this case it’s coming up into a plank position on the Reformer.
.
.
- Long stretch: maintain the body in a plank position and only pivot through the shoulder joints moving in and out of flexion and extension 
- Jackrabbit, the torso stays still, maintain neutral spine and pelvis and bend and straighten the knees and hips to move the carriage in and out. 
.
Benefits: improves upper extremity weight-bearing, core control and trunk stability, shoulder & hip dissociation & strengthening, scapula stability 💪🏼
.
.
Have your sound on and join in while I run you through a small two-minute clip! 🌟
Let me know how you go and if you enjoyed this wee demonstration and teaching series I put together, I would love to hear your feedback ☺️
